  "response_text": "Creating a fitness and diet plan for overall wellness involves a balanced approach that includes regular physical activity, a nutritious diet, and healthy lifestyle habits. Below is a sample plan that can be adjusted based on individual preferences, goals, and dietary restrictions.\n\n### Fitness Plan\n\n**Weekly Schedule:**\n- **Frequency:** Aim for at least 150 minutes of moderate aerobic activity or 75 minutes of vigorous activity each week, along with strength training at least two days a week.\n\n#### Example Weekly Routine:\n- **Monday:** \n  - *30 minutes brisk walking or jogging*\n  - *20 minutes strength training (focus on upper body)*\n  \n- **Tuesday:** \n  - *Yoga or Pilates (30-45 minutes)*\n  \n- **Wednesday:** \n  - *30 minutes cycling or swimming*\n  - *20 minutes strength training (focus on lower body)*\n  \n- **Thursday:** \n  - *Rest day or light activity (e.g., walking or stretching)*\n  \n- **Friday:** \n  - *30-45 minutes of HIIT (High-Intensity Interval Training)*\n  \n- **Saturday:** \n  - *Outdoor activity (hiking, sports, etc. for 1 hour)*\n  \n- **Sunday:** \n  - *30-60 minutes of stretching or yoga*\n\n### Diet Plan\n\n**Guidelines:**\n- Focus on whole, minimally processed foods.\n- Stay hydrated (aim for at least 8-10 cups of water daily).\n- Balance macronutrients: carbohydrates (45–65%), proteins (10–35%), and fats (20–35%).\n- Include plenty of fruits, vegetables, whole grains, lean proteins, and healthy fats.\n\n#### Sample Daily Meal Plan:\n\n**Breakfast:**\n- Oatmeal topped with fresh fruits (berries, banana) and a tablespoon of almond butter.\n- A cup of green tea or black coffee.\n\n**Morning Snack:**\n- A small handful of mixed nuts (almonds, walnuts) or a piece of fruit (apple, orange).\n\n**Lunch:**\n- Grilled chicken or tofu salad with mixed greens, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, avocado, and a vinaigrette dressing.\n- A side of whole-grain bread or quinoa.\n\n**Afternoon Snack:**\n- Greek yogurt with honey and a sprinkle of chia seeds or a small smoothie with spinach, banana, and protein powder.\n\n**Dinner:**\n- Baked salmon or chickpeas, served with steamed broccoli, brown rice, and a side salad with olive oil and lemon juice.\n  \n**Evening Snack (if needed):**\n- Carrot sticks or cucumber slices with hummus or a few squares of dark chocolate.\n\n### Additional Wellness Tips:\n\n1. **Sleep:** Aim for 7-9 hours of quality sleep each night.\n2. **Stress Management:** Incorporate mindfulness practices such as meditation, breathing exercises, or journaling.\n3. **Social Connections:** Engage with friends and family, join fitness classes, or community groups to enhance mental well-being.\n4. **Routine Check-ups:** Regular health check-ups with a healthcare provider to monitor your overall health.\n\n### Notes:\n- **Personalization:** Adjust portions and food choices based on your specific dietary needs, activity level, and preferences.\n- **Listen to Your Body:** Modify the fitness plan based on how your body feels, and consult a healthcare professional before starting any new diet or exercise program, especially if you have existing health conditions.\n\nThis plan is a general guideline and can serve as a foundation for developing a personalized approach to fitness and nutrition for overall wellness.",
